<h2>SEO</h2>

<h5>Only One h1 Tag Per Page</h5>

<p>While technically we <em>could</em> load a page up with h1 tags, it's a bad SEO practice and can cause penalties.</p>

<hr>

<h5>Use Title Attributes with Links</h5>

<p>Using a title attribute in your anchor elements will improve accessibility when used the right way.</p>

<p>It is important to understand that the title attribute should be used to increase the meaning of the anchor tag.</p>

<hr>

<h5>How Much Will A Reader Read?</h5>

<p>"A sentence should contain no unnecessary words, a paragraph no unnecessary sentences, for the same reason that a drawing should have no unnecessary lines and a machine no unnecessary parts."</p>
